29:48.740 --> 29:52.744
We have to treasure these moments.

29:55.420 --> 29:56.705
Aye.

29:58.590 --> 30:03.869
You and I ken better than most
how fleeting life can be.

30:08.090 --> 30:09.136
Hmm.

30:13.060 --> 30:16.552
Still, can't help but feel sometimes

30:16.640 --> 30:20.519
that all of this could be ripped away
at any moment.

30:20.980 --> 30:23.028
It doesn't matter, Sassenach.

30:26.910 --> 30:29.982
Don't you see
how small a thing death is between us?

30:33.910 --> 30:36.913
After you left me, after Culloden,

30:38.880 --> 30:40.074
I was dead.

30:42.050 --> 30:44.257
Yet all that time I loved you.

30:47.470 --> 30:49.176
I loved you too.

30:50.010 --> 30:51.500
I never stopped.

30:59.940 --> 31:03.603
When my body dies,
my soul will still be yours.

31:05.150 --> 31:06.856
Nothing is lost, Sassenach.

31:09.070 --> 31:10.401
Only changed.

31:16.750 --> 31:19.492
That's the first law of thermodynamics.

31:20.670 --> 31:21.910
No.

31:26.340 --> 31:27.375
No.

31:28.880 --> 31:30.120
That's faith.

31:44.820 --> 31:46.435
I don't care what it is.

31:47.190 --> 31:51.479
I want to feel alive with you right now.

33:43.980 --> 33:45.971
Do you know what lies
beyond those trees?

33:48.110 --> 33:49.099
Aye.

33:50.780 --> 33:52.065
More trees.

33:54.150 --> 33:55.697
Yes, a lot more.

33:56.450 --> 33:59.988
They stretch all the way past
a mighty river named the Mississippi

34:01.080 --> 34:02.365
to the Great Plains.

34:03.710 --> 34:06.531
This is just the start
of what America will become.

34:07.670 --> 34:10.582
Eventually, it will reach
all the way to the Pacific Ocean.

34:12.000 --> 34:16.118
North Carolina will just be
one of 50 states.

34:16.800 --> 34:17.926
Hmm.

34:19.390 --> 34:21.631
A|| filled with Scots.

34:22.890 --> 34:25.802
There will be lots
of different people here

34:25.890 --> 34:27.517
from countries all over the world.

34:27.900 --> 34:32.064
And all hoping to live
what will be called the American dream.

34:33.990 --> 34:35.446
Is that the same as our dream?

34:38.820 --> 34:40.151
I suppose it is.

34:52.460 --> 34:57.420
A chance to live in a place
where the only limitations

34:58.340 --> 35:00.217
are a person's own abilities

35:01.050 --> 35:02.756
and the will to succeed.

35:10.150 --> 35:12.687
They'll come here in their thousands.

35:14.280 --> 35:15.599
And then millions.

35:17.240 --> 35:18.696
What about those already here?

35:21.450 --> 35:22.519
The natives.

35:24.370 --> 35:25.746
What becomes of them?

35:28.290 --> 35:29.450
Well...

35:30.830 --> 35:33.799
They are driven
from their ancestral lands.

35:35.840 --> 35:36.875
They're killed.

35:38.760 --> 35:41.137
Or forced to live in reservations.

35:43.510 --> 35:46.422
It's not unlike
what the English did to the Highlanders.

35:47.560 --> 35:51.052
A dream for some
can be a nightmare for others.

36:01.110 --> 36:04.568
I suggested to Jamie
we try and sell the ruby.

36:04.870 --> 36:07.498
As we got ready
for the I/l/ington dinner that night;

36:07.830 --> 36:10.492
our hopes were h/gh
that we’d find a buyer.

36:15.840 --> 36:18.081
It's not too much mutton
dressed as lamb, is it?

36:18.710 --> 36:19.711
Neven

36:21.510 --> 36:22.795
Only thing missing...

36:24.550 --> 36:26.097
is a wee bit of jewellery.

36:29.060 --> 36:30.630
Took it to the goldsmith.

36:32.020 --> 36:35.183
Used some of our coin
to fashion this mount.

36:38.400 --> 36:40.948
Only had time
for any but the simplest design.

36:42.070 --> 36:44.618
- No, simple is best.
-Hmm.

36:48.580 --> 36:50.571
Heard Governor Tryon will be
in attendance,

36:51.250 --> 36:53.366
along with a Baron Penzler.

36:54.630 --> 36:58.122
It's said the Baron's love of money
is accompanied by a love

36:58.210 --> 37:00.087
of the fine objects that come with it.

37:00.460 --> 37:03.623
Well, let's hope
he's a fondness for rubies.

37:03.720 --> 37:04.926
Hmm.

37:11.930 --> 37:15.058
Might I request the pleasure
of your company for dinner?

37:18.980 --> 37:20.060
Madam?

37:20.150 --> 37:21.890
You may.

37:40.250 --> 37:42.582
Governor, Mrs Lillington and I
are so pleased...

37:42.670 --> 37:44.331
Four shillings poll tax...

37:44.430 --> 37:46.716
And four pence per gallon rum duty.

37:46.800 --> 37:48.381
Will it never end?

37:48.470 --> 37:50.301
That's the very least of it, Stanhope.

37:50.390 --> 37:53.348
It's the never-ending expenses
incurred in dividing our land

37:53.430 --> 37:56.149
from that of the Cherokee savages
which worries me.

37:56.230 --> 37:57.970
- All from our taxes. _
- Yes, that's a good question.

37:58.060 --> 37:59.470
It beggars belief,

38:00.730 --> 38:02.812
does it not, Mistress Fraser?

38:03.530 --> 38:05.270
Hmm, though I doubt many women

38:05.360 --> 38:08.739
_ will be familiar
With such prOVInCIal matters.

38:11.410 --> 38:13.401
Well, on the contrary,
Lord Penzler.

38:13.500 --> 38:16.162
I'm sure the very thought
of inequitable taxes

38:16.250 --> 38:18.320
brings out the savage in all of us.

38:18.420 --> 38:20.741
I'm particularly savage
when it comes to taxes

38:20.840 --> 38:22.796
that bear disproportionately
on the poor.

38:22.880 --> 38:23.869
Yes, that's very good.

38:23.970 --> 38:26.040
The savage in all of us.
Yes, indeed.

38:27.840 --> 38:29.842
You must try not to be so amusing,
Mistress Fraser.

38:29.930 --> 38:32.057
It may be the death of poor Stanhope.

38:34.430 --> 38:38.184
Is this the style in Edinburgh,
Mistress Fraser?

38:39.360 --> 38:41.225
How charming.

38:46.280 --> 38:48.020
Such a beautiful stone.

38:49.780 --> 38:51.691
You will permit me to look more closely?

38:53.240 --> 38:54.400
Certainly.

39:04.050 --> 39:05.335
Thank you.

39:08.840 --> 39:10.046
Beautiful.

39:15.020 --> 39:16.089
And without flaw.

39:18.230 --> 39:21.472
The Governor and I have heard
that you are the nephew

39:21.560 --> 39:24.529
of the Widow Cameron of River Run.

39:24.610 --> 39:26.680
Have we been informed correctly,
Mr Fraser?

39:26.780 --> 39:30.193
Aye, Jocasta Cameron is
my late mother's sister.

39:30.910 --> 39:32.571
Either of you acquainted with her?

39:32.660 --> 39:35.402
Yes, I've been acquainted
with Mistress Cameron

39:35.490 --> 39:38.573
for many years. A most charming woman.

39:39.540 --> 39:42.327
Are you familiar with her estate,
Your Excellency?

39:42.420 --> 39:45.162
Hmm, my wife and I passed several days
at Cross Creek last year

39:45.250 --> 39:47.047
during our tour of North Carolina.

39:47.130 --> 39:48.415
River Run, I believe,

39:48.510 --> 39:51.172
is situated on the Cape Fear River
at the foot of the mountains.

39:52.340 --> 39:53.420
Aye.

39:53.890 --> 39:55.767
You know, my family are Highlanders.

39:56.350 --> 39:57.886
Mountains are like home to us.

39:58.270 --> 39:59.430
Well, the Blue Ridge Mountains

39:59.520 --> 40:01.761
are some of the most majestic
you'll see anywhere, Mr Fraser.

40:02.150 --> 40:05.438
Hmm. I intend on seeing them
when I visit my aunt

40:05.520 --> 40:07.067
before returning to Scotland.

40:08.190 --> 40:09.441
Hmm.

40:12.950 --> 40:17.319
Would you join me after dinner
for a pipe and some brandy?

40:17.410 --> 40:18.866
I have a case imported from France.

40:18.950 --> 40:21.077
There's a matter I wish
to put before you.

40:31.130 --> 40:34.349
Mr Lillington tells me
you've been both a farmer and a soldier

40:34.430 --> 40:35.966
and are newly arrived to the Colonies.

40:36.350 --> 40:38.170
Are you familiar with conditions here?

40:38.560 --> 40:40.516
To which conditions
might you refer, sir?

40:42.270 --> 40:45.182
North Carolina, though not
as prosperous as its neighbours,

40:45.270 --> 40:47.067
still offers wealth and prosperity

40:47.150 --> 40:51.063
for those Willing
to persevere and work the land.

40:51.990 --> 40:56.108
The Crown encourages settlement
by industrious, God-fearing families.

40:56.910 --> 40:59.788
His Majesty is wise
to encourage settlement of lands

40:59.870 --> 41:02.361
so rich in opportunity, Your Excellency.

41:03.250 --> 41:06.788
To this end, there is established
a system of land grants

41:06.880 --> 41:09.451
whereby large acreage
may be given to men

41:09.550 --> 41:12.462
who would undertake
to persuade numbers of emigrants

41:12.550 --> 41:16.384
to come and settle on part of it
under their sponsorship.

41:17.050 --> 41:19.632
I did hear mention
of such grants, yet...

41:20.810 --> 41:23.597
Yet is it not true they come
with a steep quitrent per acre

41:23.690 --> 41:25.260
that must be paid in coin?

41:26.560 --> 41:27.686
That is true.

41:28.940 --> 41:31.488
But in frankness, Mr Fraser,

41:32.780 --> 41:34.065
there is the law,

41:34.820 --> 41:36.060
and there is What is done.

41:38.950 --> 41:41.441
It may be possible to dispense
with the requirements

41:41.540 --> 41:43.826
of quitrents
While one acquires settlers.

41:43.910 --> 41:45.787
Provided, of course,
one swears an oath of loyalty

41:45.880 --> 41:48.280
to His Majesty the King,
if not already done so.

41:49.630 --> 41:52.258
And so, not Wishing
to remind you of any past indignity,

41:52.340 --> 41:53.409
it is my duty to ask--

41:53.510 --> 41:54.750
And mine to answer.

41:59.970 --> 42:01.517
I'm a pardoned Jacobite.

42:02.640 --> 42:03.880
I've sworn the oath.

42:05.100 --> 42:08.058
Like so many others that paid
that price to keep their lives.

42:10.400 --> 42:12.140
It's late, Your Excellency.

42:12.940 --> 42:14.646
I must beg to take my leave of you.

42:14.740 --> 42:16.776
Well, good night, Mr Fraser.

42:16.860 --> 42:18.066
Um...

42:18.450 --> 42:19.860
Do consider my offer.

42:35.800 --> 42:37.961
A hundred pounds sterling.

42:38.050 --> 42:39.847
For a single ruby, all thanks to you.

42:41.180 --> 42:44.638
The Baron nearly dropped his eyeballs
into your bosom, the filthy lech.

42:44.730 --> 42:46.937
Had a right mind
to challenge him over it.

42:47.310 --> 42:49.722
Discretion is the better part of valour,

42:49.810 --> 42:52.062
though I've yet to meet a Scot
who seemed to think so.

42:52.150 --> 42:53.276
Hmm.

42:53.730 --> 42:55.231
Be that as it may,

42:55.820 --> 42:57.651
the Baron's eye for fine gemstones

42:57.740 --> 43:00.447
means we've enough money
to secure passage

43:00.530 --> 43:02.236
to Scotland many times over.

43:03.620 --> 43:05.247
With What's left over, I can...

43:06.710 --> 43:09.076
I can purchase a printing press.

43:09.170 --> 43:10.910
You can practice your healing.

43:19.180 --> 43:21.967
Dinna fash, Sassenach. It'll be fine.

43:22.810 --> 43:25.973
John Grey used his influence
to Withdraw the warrant.

43:26.430 --> 43:28.057
I'm no longer a wanted man.

43:29.270 --> 43:33.183
- It's not that.
- You're a terrible liar.

43:34.400 --> 43:35.606
- No, it's nothing.
- Ha.

43:35.730 --> 43:37.812
Thinking so loudly,
I can hear ye from here.

43:40.910 --> 43:44.482
Well, I was thinking about the offer
the Governor made to you.

43:47.120 --> 43:48.200
Aye.

43:49.370 --> 43:51.247
I was thinking on the matter myself.

43:52.460 --> 43:53.449
And?

43:54.130 --> 43:55.165
Huh.

43:56.050 --> 44:00.589
Oh, he's no' offering me land
for the sake of my bonny blue eyes.

44:01.050 --> 44:04.349
Bees that have honey in their mouth
have a sting in their tail.

44:07.020 --> 44:08.635
Ask yourself this.

44:09.640 --> 44:10.629
Why me?

44:10.980 --> 44:14.143
_ _ An outsider _
With few ties and no known loyalties.

44:16.070 --> 44:19.949
Except to the man that's offering you
a large tract of land.

44:20.030 --> 44:21.156
Hmm.

44:21.320 --> 44:24.369
The man's a soldier. A man of strategy.

44:25.120 --> 44:26.530
He kens me as one.

44:27.540 --> 44:30.703
And I understand he's had trouble
with the Regulators

44:30.790 --> 44:32.075
a year past.

44:33.920 --> 44:35.285
Who are the Regulators?

44:35.590 --> 44:37.330
They're men from the Wilderness.

44:38.210 --> 44:39.461
They've taken offence
at What they believe

44:39.550 --> 44:42.963
is illegal behaviour on the part
of Tryon's tax collectors.

44:43.550 --> 44:45.791
So they've taken matters
into their own hands.

44:46.100 --> 44:50.059
They've called meetings,
drawn up petitions,

44:50.140 --> 44:52.096
stirred up a spirit of resistance.

44:52.900 --> 44:54.390
The Governor's clearly worried.

44:55.980 --> 44:57.641
So, if things heat up,

44:57.730 --> 44:59.277
he wants to buy
the loyalty and obligation

44:59.360 --> 45:00.566
of an experienced soldier,

45:00.650 --> 45:03.858
all for the cost of a few acres
of the King's land. Hmm.

45:04.660 --> 45:06.366
He's much sneakier than I thought.

45:06.950 --> 45:08.190
He's practically Scottish.

45:09.240 --> 45:10.241
No.

45:13.500 --> 45:15.741
Oh, Jamie, you have to remember

45:15.880 --> 45:18.087
there's going to be
another war in eight years.

45:19.050 --> 45:20.415
The American Revolution.

45:21.380 --> 45:24.383
If you accepted the Governor's
offer of the land,

45:24.760 --> 45:27.923
he'd expect you to fight for the Crown
against the revolutionaries.

45:28.430 --> 45:30.512
I've fought in wars before, Sassenach.

45:30.720 --> 45:34.724
Yes, but unlike Culloden,
this one the British Will lose.

45:35.850 --> 45:38.102
We would be
on the wrong side of history again.

45:38.730 --> 45:40.937
We would be branded as loyalists,

45:41.030 --> 45:42.770
and the land the Governor
has offered you

45:43.610 --> 45:44.986
would be taken from us.

45:49.160 --> 45:53.073
This becomes Brianna's country,
does it not?

45:56.920 --> 45:58.490
Yes, she was born here.

46:01.550 --> 46:03.836
I dinna Wish to fight in wars again...

46:05.130 --> 46:07.212
or have you in danger, Sassenach,

46:09.560 --> 46:12.461
but if there's a bit I can do
to make this a good land

46:13.480 --> 46:14.629
for Brianna...

46:15.810 --> 46:18.938
If my presence here now
can be felt by her later, then...

46:21.360 --> 46:22.896
Then that would be something.

46:27.990 --> 46:29.230
Yes, it would.

46:37.080 --> 46:40.083
Ian? Ian, where have you been?

46:41.300 --> 46:42.870
And what's this beast you have With you?

46:43.170 --> 46:45.081
Isn't he a handsome dog, Uncle?

46:45.300 --> 46:46.756
Don't think that's a dog, Ian.

46:47.260 --> 46:49.251
More like a bloody wolf.

46:49.340 --> 46:51.968
Broader through the head
and chest than a wolf.

46:52.060 --> 46:53.925
He's a fine creature.
Where'd you get him?

46:54.020 --> 46:55.055
I won him.

46:55.770 --> 46:57.135
Luclq roll of the dice.

46:58.560 --> 47:00.050
So I called him Rollo.

47:02.110 --> 47:03.145
Ye were dicin'?

47:05.070 --> 47:07.061
Aye, with sailors.

47:07.610 --> 47:09.908
But he's not the only thing I won.

47:12.700 --> 47:17.069
Christ, ye shouldn't stake yer life
gambling with sailors.

47:17.460 --> 47:18.950
But you're always at it, Uncle.

47:19.040 --> 47:21.782
Every tavern we've seen fit to rest,
you've wagered our coin.

47:22.130 --> 47:23.950
That's cards, not dice.

47:24.050 --> 47:25.586
And I ken What I'm doing.

47:25.670 --> 47:27.410
Well, I won, did I no'?

47:27.510 --> 47:29.250
We have need of the money
for the journey home.

47:30.970 --> 47:33.131
Aye, well,
if your mother hears of this...

47:34.310 --> 47:36.551
I won't do it again. Promise.

47:37.390 --> 47:39.972
You're right, you won't.
And you won't need to.

47:40.060 --> 47:41.220
We've plenty of money now.

47:41.310 --> 47:43.221
We found a buyer
for the ruby last night.

47:43.320 --> 47:45.106
Well, that's some good news, Auntie.

47:45.320 --> 47:49.063
Aye, well, bring your mongrel
and we'll go inside.

47:49.320 --> 47:50.400
We'll have some food.

47:51.570 --> 47:53.777
Then there's some things
we need to talk about.

47:58.790 --> 48:00.109
Come on, Rollo.

48:10.720 --> 48:12.961
Staying in America?

48:15.600 --> 48:16.635
Aye.

48:17.350 --> 48:20.558
Aye, Claire and I have decided
to try and make a life here.

48:20.770 --> 48:22.476
That's a fine idea.

48:22.770 --> 48:23.930
- We could stay--
- Not we, lad.

48:24.020 --> 48:25.760
Ye'll still be on a ship
bound for Scotland.

48:25.860 --> 48:27.521
Oh, please, Uncle.

48:27.610 --> 48:29.066
I'll not be a worry to ye.

48:29.150 --> 48:30.560
Truly, I swear it.

48:30.650 --> 48:31.947
I'll work to earn my bread.

48:32.030 --> 48:34.578
I've a talent for selling.
Fergus will tell ye.

48:35.490 --> 48:37.731
Ye ken I would like nothing more
than to have ye with me,

48:37.830 --> 48:40.651
but in What God's name
would your mother say?

48:41.080 --> 48:42.411
Oh, I dinna ken.

48:43.960 --> 48:45.700
But she'll be saying it in Scotland,
won't she?

48:47.590 --> 48:48.955
She kens I'm safe with ye.

48:49.050 --> 48:50.790
Ye wrote to her back in Georgia.

48:50.880 --> 48:52.962
I canna say
that particular bit of knowledge

48:53.050 --> 48:56.213
will be over-comforting to her, Ian.

48:57.140 --> 48:59.677
Your parents dinna want
a vagrant's life for you, lad.

48:59.770 --> 49:02.512
They want you to grow to be
a man of learning and influence.

49:02.600 --> 49:03.976
A man of worth.

49:05.690 --> 49:08.067
You'll amount to something
for yer mother's sake.

49:08.730 --> 49:10.231
If it kills us both.

49:11.820 --> 49:13.776
Yer life's no meant
to be wasted.

49:18.080 --> 49:19.149
Where will you settle?

49:21.960 --> 49:24.360
We thought we would work that out
when we're visiting River Run.

49:24.460 --> 49:25.495
Mmm.

49:26.080 --> 49:30.915
Fergus, I want ye to have
a portion of the profit from the ruby.

49:31.760 --> 49:34.672
It will pay for ye and Marsali to return
to Scotland, if that's What you choose.

49:35.930 --> 49:38.592
And there's a bit
for Marsali to take home to her mother.

49:39.100 --> 49:40.965
For the alimony I promised.

49:43.560 --> 49:45.391
There's enough for you as well, Lesley.

49:47.230 --> 49:49.061
I appreciate it, Mac Dubh.

49:50.400 --> 49:55.315
But I'd have ye keep your coin
if I may travel with ye a bit longer.

49:58.030 --> 50:02.319
This is a Wild country,
and... my place is at your side.

50:05.210 --> 50:07.166
Aye, ye may.

50:08.540 --> 50:12.044
We would like to stay
in North Carolina as well, Milord.

50:12.960 --> 50:15.428
Marsali would not be well-suited
to a long journey.

50:22.430 --> 50:23.761
She is with child.

50:26.770 --> 50:27.805
What?

50:29.980 --> 50:32.778
Well, it certainly is a happy surprise.

50:32.860 --> 50:35.192
Aye, was a surprise
to us as well.

50:38.070 --> 50:41.073
Of course, we are delighted.

50:41.660 --> 50:43.696
May God bless you both.

50:45.710 --> 50:48.076
For now,
Marsali and I will stay in Wilmington.

50:48.170 --> 50:50.377
It's a wee bit bigger than Broch Mordha.

50:50.670 --> 50:52.956
I hope to find work as a seamstress,

50:53.340 --> 50:55.661
While Fergus seeks employment himself.

50:55.760 --> 50:57.500
Aye, you'll do fine, Marsali.

50:57.590 --> 51:00.002
And you, you'll make a fine father.

51:00.970 --> 51:02.346
Thank you, Milord.

51:04.640 --> 51:07.097
Campagnia
leaves in under a fortnight.

51:07.190 --> 51:09.932
You two will accompany us
to River Run until then.

51:18.570 --> 51:21.312
- Congratulations. Great news.
- Thanks.

51:43.470 --> 51:45.426
So, What is your Aunt Jocasta like?

51:49.190 --> 51:50.179
She's a MacKenzie.

51:50.400 --> 51:51.640
Hmm.

51:52.480 --> 51:53.890
She's my mother's sister.

51:54.610 --> 51:56.771
And I haven't seen her
Since I was a wee lad.

51:57.320 --> 52:00.812
She wed a John Cameron and left Leoch
before my parents married.

52:01.740 --> 52:03.230
She's never visited Lallybroch?

52:04.410 --> 52:05.729
Aye, once or twice.

52:07.040 --> 52:11.249
Then, John died of a flux,
so she wed his cousin, Hugh Cameron.

52:12.250 --> 52:14.627
Well, he was killed hunting.

52:15.420 --> 52:18.082
So, then she wed Hector Cameron.

52:20.550 --> 52:22.632
Well, she seems to have quite
the taste for Camerons.

52:22.760 --> 52:23.749
Hmm.

52:23.850 --> 52:26.171
Is there something special
about them as a clan?

52:26.260 --> 52:28.558
Outside from being accident-prone.

52:29.180 --> 52:32.013
Well, they have a way wi' words.

52:32.600 --> 52:35.012
Camerons are poets and jesters.

52:35.270 --> 52:37.977
So which is Hector? A poet or a jester?

52:38.280 --> 52:39.429
Neither.

52:40.450 --> 52:41.485
He's dead now, too.

52:45.330 --> 52:47.901
So, how did they come
to be in North Carolina?

52:47.990 --> 52:51.619
Well, after the Rising, he and Jocasta
fled Scotland and came here.

52:52.920 --> 52:57.835
He was granted land, built a house
and a saw mill, planted tobacco.

52:58.510 --> 53:01.877
And then he died
of a morbid sore throat a year past.

53:05.300 --> 53:10.010
Well, I hope the messenger arrives
with your letter before we do.

53:11.390 --> 53:13.642
He'd arrive before we do
if he crawled on his hands and knees.

53:15.520 --> 53:16.646
Well, keep going, lad.

53:16.980 --> 53:19.938
I expect ye'll have us
in River Run before nightfall.

53:27.080 --> 53:28.445
